  "texts": [
    "As expected, taking more posterior samples increases runtime roughly linearly, since inference repeats the sampling loop more times.",
    "C. Imputation AccuracyFigure 7 shows the MAE across varying missingness rates for the wine and energy datasets.",
    "As expected, higher missingness consistently leads to higher MAE across all methods, because with fewer observed entries, models have less information to infer dependencies between attributes, reducing the accuracy of the reconstructed values.At 30% missingness (Tables II-III), MAE generally increases from MCAR to MNAR.",
    "Exceptions appear in housing, where strong feature collinearity allows MAR/M-NAR imputations to outperform MCAR.",
    "MIWAE achieves the best accuracy because its multiple-sampling and importanceweighting approach allows it to better approximate the true data distribution and produce more reliable imputations."
